scene_description_enriched: The upper register depicts Saint Catherine of Alexandria, crowned and with a halo, praying with clasped hands. To her right, two men are engaged in a struggle, one appearing to be subdued by the other. In the background, a group of figures stands watching. The lower register shows a man in armor raising a sword to behead a kneeling woman, also with a halo, who is praying with clasped hands. Behind her, a building complex resembling a castle or fortified town is visible. The scene is set in a landscape with trees and hills. The inscription below the upper scene reads 'D. Sancta Katharina'.
